The paper deals with the efficient approximability of graph and logic problems, which are typically studied in the computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. The use of hierarchical and periodic specifications also suggests a possible connection to computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the fact that the problems considered are PSPACE-hard may indicate a link to the area of logic and computation (cs.LO).
